article.headline: IOWA 64, (24) IOWA ST 39
article.linkText: Bluder wins 400th game as Iowa routs Iowa State 64-39
article.story:
IOWA CITY, Iowa (Ticker) -- The balance of power in the 
Hawkeye state has shifted.

Jennie Lillis collected 24 points and 10 rebounds as Iowa ended
a five-game skid against No. 24 Iowa State with a 64-39 rout.

Iowa State (1-2) has been the more successful program recently
but dropped its second straight to a state opponent after a loss
to Drake last week. The Cyclones managed just six baskets in
the second half.

The win gave Iowa coach Lisa Bluder her 400th victory. She is
400-163 in her 19 years of coaching.

Iowa (5-1) shot just 39 percent (12-of-31) from the field in the
first half for a 30-25 halftime cushion.  The Hawkeyes used
their defense to overwhelm the Cyclones in the second half.

Lindsay Richards scored 11 points and added five assists for
Iowa. Jamie Cavey added six rebounds as the Hawkeye held a 44-32
edge on the glass.

Lindsey Wilson scored 15 points and was the only Cyclone in
double figures.
